        arises from probable existence of no less than four writers of this name)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Anderson, G. Philostratus, 1986: index (Philostratus the Athenian) p. 3 
    (a sophist, b. somewhere around the 170s, the Suda puts his death in the reign of Philip the
        Arab (244-9), the 2nd in a line of 4 (or 1st of 3) Philostrati from Lemnos, the ascription 
        of the Lives of the sophists gives the author's name as Flavius Philostratus, epigraphic
        evidence enables us to add at least tentatively a praenomen Lucius)</mads:note>
